To remove litter:
	for A in . conf contrib crypt doc getopt src; do \
		(cd $A; rm `cat .cvsignore`); done

Release checklist

 1.  Perform a `make maintainer-clean` and remove any litter
 2.  Check it compiles and runs --enable-debug
 3.  Perform a `make maintainer-clean` and remove any litter
 4.  Check it compiles and runs without any flags
 5.  Fix any bugs/warnings, commit them, and return to 1
 6.  Perform a `make maintainer-clean` and remove any litter
 7.  Run `cvs2cl.pl --gmt --prune -U AUTHORS.map -l '-b'` to create new
     ChangeLog.  If this is a non-head branch replace the "-l 'b'" with
     "-F BRANCH-x_x".
 8.  `rm ChangeLog.bak`
 9.  `cvs diff ChangeLog > changes.txt`
10.  Edit changes.txt and undiffify it.
11.  Read changes.txt and write summary.txt from it
12.  Write release.txt including summary.txt after an
     "-----Official Summary-----" marker.
13.  Edit the NEWS file, add in new version and any config/use changes
14.  Check the TODO file is up to date
15.  Adjust the Features list in the README file if necessary.  This will also
     require the adjustment of the website's index.html.in file.
16.  Any changes to INSTALL?  Do them and adjust website's install.html file.
17.  Do a general `cvs commit -m "Version x.x.x released."`
18.  do a `cvs tag RELEASE-x_x_x`
19.  do an `autogen.sh` without any flags
20.  make dist
21.  FTP dist file to ftp://upload.sourceforge.net/incoming
22.  `gpg --armor --comment 'See http://dircproxy.sourceforge.net/\
      download.html for more information' --detach-sign DISTFILE`
23.  scp dist file and asc file to keybuk@dircproxy.sourceforge.net:\
     /home/groups/ftp/pub/dircproxy/source
24.  Remove 'src' directory from dircproxy and replace with new version
25.  Add new file release on sourceforge supplying changes.txt and summary.txt
26.  Add new news item title "dircproxy x.x.x released" containing release.txt
27.  Run build-site.pl on dircproxy.sourceforge.net to ensure the site always
     carries the latest information.
28.  Check the site front page, news page and download page.
29.  Announce new version on freshmeat using summary.txt
30.  E-mail dircproxy-announce list with release.txt making sure to sign
     the e-mail.
31.  E-Mail nidd@debian.org and greid@ukug.uk.freebsd.org with any significant
     changes that could affect packaging (new files etc), making sure to sign
     the e-mail.
32.  Edit configure.in & contrib/dircproxy.spec and increment the version
     number, commit with message "CVS version now x.x.x"
